quran[8]{c,v,t,f}:
  33,36,"It is not for any believing man or believing woman, when Allah and His Messenger have decreed a command, to have a choice in their affair. And whoever disobeys Allah and His Messenger, then he has strayed into evident misguidance."
  33,37,"And recall as you say to the one upon whom Allah had bestowed His grace, and upon whom you<sup>sg </sup>had<i>(also) </i>bestowed your grace, “Hold on to your spouse and be mindful of Allah,” while hiding within yourself what Allah was to reveal, and fearing mankind, whereas Allah is more worthy of your fear. Then when Zaid ended his relationship with her{1}, We married her to you, that there may be no blame on the believers regarding the spouses of their adopted sons when their relationship has ended, for the command of Allah has always been fulfilled.",1:[By divorce.]
  33,38,"Never has there been any blame on the Prophet regarding what Allah has ordained for him; such is Allah’s rule among those<i>(prophets) </i>who passed on before, and the command of Allah has always been a determined determination."
  33,39,"Those who proclaim the messages of Allah and fear Him and fear no one except Allah. And Allah is sufficient as a Reckoner."
  33,40,"Never has Muhammad been the father of any of your<sup>pl </sup>men, but a Messenger of Allah and the seal{1}of the prophets. And Allah has always been All-Knowing of everything.",1:[Qira’at: All except for Asem read it as: “…the sealer of the prophets.”]
  33,41,"O you who have attained faith, remember Allah with frequent remembrance,"
  33,42,"and highly exalt Him morning and evening."
  33,43,"It is He Who blesses you<sup>pl </sup>, as do His angels{1}, to get you out of darkness<i>(es) </i>into light, and He has always been Merciful to the believers.",1:[Angels bless people by praying to God for them.]
